<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="71" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 907/31–32.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Wilson</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-06-14"><hi rend="italic">June 14,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 110.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            Nos. 167 and 175, dated respectively April 7 and May 7 last, and to
                            inform you that the question of the employment of state agents to induce
                            immigration from Europe is receiving the consideration of the Department
                            of Commerce and Labor, and that when a conclusion is reached in the
                            matter you will be informed thereof.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>